# @version ^0.2.16
# contracts/Employment.vy

# Setup private variables (only callable from within the contract)

"""
struct EmploymentContract:
    employer: address
    employee: address
    contract_value: uint256
    severance_percent: decimal
    period: uint256
    grace: uint256
    accepted: bool
    severance: uint256
    contract_start: uint256
    next_payment: uint256

"""

struct ContractEndProposal:
    employer_status: int128
    employee_status: int128
    init_time: uint256

employer: public(address)
employee: public(address)
contract_value: public(uint256)
severance_percent: public(uint256)
period: public(uint256)
grace: public(uint256)
accepted: public(int128)
severance: public(uint256)
contract_start: public(uint256)
next_payment: public(uint256)

end_proposal: public(ContractEndProposal)

PLATFROM_FEE_PERCENT: constant(uint256) = 1

    

@external
@payable
def setup(_employer: address, _employee: address, _contract_value: uint256, _severance_percent: uint256, _period: uint256, _grace: uint256):
    assert _contract_value == msg.value
    assert _severance_percent >= 0 and _severance_percent+PLATFROM_FEE_PERCENT <= 100
    assert _period > 0

    self.employer = _employer
    self.employee = _employee
    self.contract_value = _contract_value
    self.severance_percent = _severance_percent
    self.period = _period
    self.grace = _grace
    self.contract_start = block.timestamp
    self.next_payment = block.timestamp + _period
    self.accepted = 0
    self.severance = 0

    
@external
def accept():
    assert self.employee == msg.sender
    assert self.accepted == 0
    
    self.accepted = 1
    
@external
def decline():
    assert self.employee == msg.sender or self.employer == msg.sender
    assert self.accepted == 0
    
    self.accepted = 2
    send(self.employer, self.contract_value)

@internal
def uint_rounded_div(n: uint256, d: uint256) -> uint256:
    return n/d + n%d / (d-d/2)

@external
@payable
def pay():
    assert self.employer == msg.sender
    assert self.contract_value <= msg.value
    assert self.accepted == 1
    assert block.timestamp <= self.next_payment + self.grace
    
    value_received: decimal = convert(msg.value, decimal)
    percentage_point_value: decimal = value_received / 100.
    taxes_decimal: decimal = percentage_point_value * convert(self.severance_percent, decimal)
    platform_fee_decimal: decimal = percentage_point_value * convert(PLATFROM_FEE_PERCENT, decimal)

    taxes: uint256 = convert(floor(taxes_decimal), uint256)
    platform_fee: uint256 = convert(floor(platform_fee_decimal), uint256)
    salary: uint256 = msg.value - taxes - platform_fee
    
    self.next_payment = self.next_payment + self.period
    self.severance = self.severance + taxes

    send(self.employee, salary)
    #send(platform_address, platform_fee)

@external
def contract_end_proposal():
    assert block.timestamp <= self.next_payment + self.grace
    assert self.accepted == 1
    assert self.employee == msg.sender or self.employer == msg.sender
    assert self.end_proposal.employer_status == 0 and self.end_proposal.employee_status == 0
    
    if self.employee == msg.sender:
        self.end_proposal = ContractEndProposal({employer_status: 0, employee_status: 1, init_time: block.timestamp})
        
    if self.employer == msg.sender:
        self.end_proposal = ContractEndProposal({employer_status: 1, employee_status: 0, init_time: block.timestamp})

@internal
def _calc_deposit_split(is_employer: bool, time_difference: uint256) -> uint256:
    time_split: uint256 = time_difference
    
    if not is_employer:
        time_split = self.period - time_split

    salary_leftovers_split: uint256 = 0

    if time_split > 0:
    	# Clip time percent to [0, 100]
        time_percent: uint256 = self.uint_rounded_div(time_split * 100, self.period)
        salary_leftovers_split = self.uint_rounded_div(self.contract_value * time_percent, 100)
        
    return salary_leftovers_split

@internal
def _calc_severance_peaceful_split() -> uint256:
    severance_split: uint256 = 0
    
    if self.severance > 0:
        severance_split = self.uint_rounded_div(self.severance, 2)

    return severance_split

@external
def contract_end_accept():
    assert self.end_proposal.employer_status + self.end_proposal.employee_status == 1, "End proposal status is incorrect"
    assert self.end_proposal.init_time + self.grace >= block.timestamp, "End proposal timed out"
    assert self.employee == msg.sender or self.employer == msg.sender, "Sender incorrect"

    if self.end_proposal.employer_status == 1 and self.end_proposal.employee_status == 0:
        assert self.employee == msg.sender, "Sender incorrect"
        self.end_proposal.employee_status = 1

    if self.end_proposal.employer_status == 0 and self.end_proposal.employee_status == 1:
        assert self.employer == msg.sender, "Sender incorrect"
        self.end_proposal.employer_status = 1

    time_before_next_payment: uint256 = 0

    if self.next_payment > self.end_proposal.init_time:
        time_before_next_payment = self.next_payment - self.end_proposal.init_time

    employer_deposit_part: uint256 = self._calc_deposit_split(True, time_before_next_payment)
    employee_deposit_part: uint256 = self._calc_deposit_split(False, time_before_next_payment)

    severance_split: uint256 = self._calc_severance_peaceful_split()
        
    employer_split: uint256 = employer_deposit_part + severance_split
    employee_split: uint256 = employee_deposit_part + severance_split

    if employer_split > 0:
        send(self.employer, employer_split)

    if employee_split > 0:
        send(self.employee, employee_split)

    #Self destruct?
    
@external
def contract_end_decline():
    assert self.end_proposal.employer_status + self.end_proposal.employee_status == 1
    assert self.end_proposal.init_time + self.grace >= block.timestamp
    assert self.employee == msg.sender or self.employer == msg.sender

    employer_split: uint256 = 0
    employee_split: uint256 = 0

    if self.end_proposal.employer_status == 1 and self.end_proposal.employee_status == 0:
        assert self.employee == msg.sender
        
        employee_split = employee_split + self.severance
        self.end_proposal.employee_status = 2

    if self.end_proposal.employer_status == 0 and self.end_proposal.employee_status == 1:
        assert self.employer == msg.sender
        
        employer_split = employer_split + self.severance
        self.end_proposal.employer_status = 2

    time_before_next_payment: uint256 = 0

    if self.next_payment > self.end_proposal.init_time:
       	time_before_next_payment = self.next_payment - self.end_proposal.init_time

    employer_deposit_part: uint256 = self._calc_deposit_split(True, time_before_next_payment)
    employee_deposit_part: uint256 = self._calc_deposit_split(False, time_before_next_payment)

    employer_split = employer_split + employer_deposit_part
    employee_split = employee_split + employee_deposit_part

    if employer_split > 0:
        send(self.employer, employer_split)

    if employee_split > 0:
        send(self.employee, employee_split)
    
    #Self destruct?

    #One party didn't accepted
    #Send severance to party that didn't accepted
    #Send employee compensation for days passed this month
    #Send employer the leftovers of compensation

@external
def update_contract_status():
    assert self.employee == msg.sender or self.employer == msg.sender
    
    employer_split: uint256 = 0
    employee_split: uint256 = 0
    
    if self.end_proposal.employer_status + self.end_proposal.employee_status == 1 and block.timestamp > self.end_proposal.init_time + self.grace:
        # Should it be auto-accepted or auto-declined?
        if self.end_proposal.employer_status == 1 and self.end_proposal.employee_status == 0:
            employee_split = employee_split + self.severance
            self.end_proposal.employee_status = 3

        if self.end_proposal.employer_status == 0 and self.end_proposal.employee_status == 1:
            employer_split = employer_split + self.severance
            self.end_proposal.employer_status = 3

        time_before_next_payment: uint256 = 0

        if self.next_payment > self.end_proposal.init_time:
        	time_before_next_payment = self.next_payment - self.end_proposal.init_time

        employer_split = employer_split + self._calc_deposit_split(True, time_before_next_payment)
        employee_split = employee_split + self._calc_deposit_split(False, time_before_next_payment)

        #selfdestruct

    elif block.timestamp > self.next_payment + self.grace:
    	#_calc_deposit_split will not gonna work unles end proposal initiated
        employer_split = self._calc_deposit_split(True, 0)
        employee_split = self.severance + self._calc_deposit_split(False, 0)

        #selfdestruct?

    if employer_split > 0:
        send(self.employer, employer_split)

    if employee_split > 0:
        send(self.employee, employee_split)
